💚Brand New 5 Minute ⏱️Workout 💚 
This is now available on my YouTube Channel  @ (📺 Lucy Wyndham-Read) 

This focuses on developing you a strong core and we do this by targeting your internal and external obliques (waist muscles) and working the deep core muscle known as your Transverse Abdominus.
By doing the moves standing ensures all your ab muscles are worked.

As a trainer I am always learning and years ago we did focus on abs on the floor (but like everything we evolve and with new research we find better and more effective methods) Standing abs allows you to have a fuller range of motion- (as well as improving your balance, posture, heart health and flexibility)

So nowadays I say a jump off the floor to work your core - (plus less strain on neck and back)

Tip 🙅🏼‍♀️Engage all 3 Planes of Motion to get a stronger and healthier body 🙅🏼‍♀️

So many workouts just use Sagittal for example:
Plank 
Burpees
High Knees
Squats
Lunges 

This causes an overload and this is why it is important to use Multiple Directional Moves and engage Lateral (also known as frontal) and Transverse moves to your routine.✔️

By using all 3 is how we keep good alignment, muscular balance, prevent injury and get way better results.

Mobility exercises are an essential part of maintaining joint health. 

They involve movements that improve the range of motion and flexibility of your joints. You can daily follow my Free (on YouTube)
5-Minute Mobility Workout ➡️ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bpsoqk8v_bE

Here are some of the Benefits you will get from this workout:

🤍Increased synovial fluid circulation🤍Synovial fluid lubricates the joints, reducing friction and allowing smooth movement. Mobility exercises help circulate this fluid, ensuring that the joints are adequately lubricated. Improved circulation of synovial fluid can enhance joint function and reduce the risk of cartilage degeneration.

🤍Improved flexibility 🤍
Regular mobility exercises can increase joint flexibility by stretching the surrounding muscles, tendons, and ligaments. This increased flexibility helps reduce stiffness and maintains or improves the joint’s range of motion.

🤍Enhanced blood flow🤍
Engaging in mobility exercises stimulates blood flow to the joints, which promotes the delivery of essential nutrients and oxygen. Increased blood circulation aids in tissue repair and reduces inflammation, contributing to overall joint health. 🤍Strengthening supporting structures🤍
Many mobility exercises target the muscles, tendons, and ligaments surrounding the joints. Strengthening these supporting structures provides stability to the joints and reduces the strain on them during movement. Strong muscles can help alleviate stress on the joints, preventing injuries and degenerative conditions.

🤍Prevention of joint stiffness🤍
Inactivity and sedentary lifestyles can lead to joint stiffness. Regular mobility exercises help combat this by promoting joint movement and preventing the development of stiffness. By keeping the joints mobile, you reduce the likelihood of experiencing discomfort and improve your ability to perform daily activities.

💕Exercise really is medicine💕

Balance exercises are key 🔑 for our overall health✔️💙 I have created you this 2 Minute Balance Routine that you can do daily to help improve your balance just using 3 moves 💃

And here are just a few reasons why we need to look after ours:

💙 Helps Fall Prevention: Balance exercises help improve stability and reduce the risk of falls, especially in older adults. By strengthening the muscles involved in balance and improving coordination, these exercises can enhance proprioception (awareness of body position) and help maintain equilibrium, reducing the likelihood of accidents.

💙 Builds Core Strength and Stability: Many balance exercises engage the core muscles, including the abdominal and back muscles. A strong core provides a stable foundation for movement and improves overall body control and posture. 
💙 Helps Joint Stability: Balance exercises can help strengthen the muscles around joints, such as the ankles, knees, and hips. This increased muscular stability can enhance joint integrity and reduce the risk of injuries, particularly during activities that involve sudden movements or changes in direction. 
💙 Improves Functional Movements: Balance exercises mimic real-life movements and challenges, making them highly applicable to daily activities. Improved balance can enhance activities such as walking, climbing stairs, bending, and reaching, making these tasks easier and reducing the risk of injury. 
The list goes on but in summary, balance exercises offer a wide range of benefits, including fall prevention, improved core strength, joint stability, enhanced athletic performance, functional movement, better posture, and increased mind-body connection. Regular practice of these exercises can contribute to overall physical well-being and functional ability.

NO JUMP CARDIO MOVES 💚

Engaging in exercises that involve minimal or no jumping can be considered safer for your joints for several reasons ✔️ 
💚Lower risk of overuse injuries: Continuous jumping or high-impact activities can put excessive strain on the joints, tendons, and ligaments. Over time, this repetitive stress can lead to overuse injuries, such as tendinitis or stress fractures. By opting for exercises without jumping, you decrease the likelihood of developing these types of injuries. 
💚Joint stability: Certain jumping exercises require a significant amount of joint stabilization, especially in the lower body. If you have pre-existing joint issues or weak stabilizing muscles, these exercises may further compromise joint stability and potentially lead to accidents or injuries. 

💚Non-jumping exercises typically have a lower demand for joint stabilization, making them a safer option for individuals with joint concerns. 
💚Joint conditions or limitations: People with specific joint conditions or limitations may find jumping exercises uncomfortable or risky. For example, individuals with osteoarthritis, joint pain, or previous joint injuries may experience increased discomfort or potential aggravation of their condition when performing high-impact exercises. 

💚In such cases, non-jumping exercises provide a safer alternative to maintain fitness without exacerbating joint problems.

What is the best exercises for Perimenopause 💁🏼‍♀️

💃Embracing a healthy and active lifestyle during perimenopause is one of the best ways to help reduce Perimenopause Symptoms.

 🌸Here are some of the best moves to help boost metabolic health, joint health, bone health, cardiovascular health as well as mental health. 🌸

🌸As women undergo the transitional phase of perimenopause, maintaining a regular exercise routine becomes crucial for overall well-being🌸

🌸 Multi Compound Moves 🌸
Compound exercises allow you to work multiple muscle groups simultaneously, making them highly time-efficient. Instead of performing isolated exercises for each muscle group, you can target several areas at once, reducing the time needed to complete a full-body workout. Plus Core Activation and Stability:
Many compound moves require core stabilization to maintain proper form. As a result, you develop a strong and stable core, which is essential for good posture, balance, and injury prevention

🌸Bodyweight Training🌸
Incorporate bodyweight (also known as strength) training exercises into your routine to maintain muscle mass and bone density, which can be affected during perimenopause. Bodyweight exercises like squats, lunges and push-ups are excellent options to enhance strength and tone muscles.

🌸Multi Directional Moves 🌸
Combat stiffness and improve flexibility by increasing range of motion, reduce muscle tension, and promote relaxation during this transitional phase.

💤Exercise for Better Sleep💤
During perimenopause, sleep disturbances can become more prevalent. Engaging in regular physical activity can help improve sleep quality. Aim for workouts earlier in the day, as exercising too close to bedtime may interfere with sleep patterns.

A recent study found that 4000 Steps a Day will help for better health ✔️ so if you have always been put off by the thought of doing 10,000 steps a day then this is great news for you. 

Throughout my career as a Trainer I have always said Walking is the No1 Exercise and here are just some of the reasons:

💚Accessibility and Low Impact: Walking requires no special equipment or training. It is a low-impact exercise, which means it puts minimal stress on your joints compared to activities like running. This makes it suitable for people of all fitness levels, ages, and physical conditions. 
💚Cardiovascular Health: Walking increases your heart rate and improves cardiovascular fitness. It helps strengthen your heart and lungs, reduces the risk of heart disease, lowers blood pressure, and improves circulation.

💚Mental Health: Walking has been shown to have positive effects on mental health. It can help reduce stress, anxiety, and depression. The act of walking outdoors, especially in natural environments, can have a calming and mood-enhancing effect. 
💚Bone Health: Weight-bearing activities like walking can help maintain and improve bone density, reducing the risk of conditions like osteoporosis. 
💚Joint Health: Walking can help lubricate joints and improve their flexibility, reducing the risk of joint-related issues.

💚Consistency: One of the keys to any successful exercise routine is consistency. Walking is an activity that most people can easily incorporate into their daily lives, increasing the likelihood of maintaining a regular exercise habit.

Fun Facts About Your Trainer 🙅🏼‍♀️ and Why YOU Should Keep Chasing YOUR Dreams.✔️

⚪️ During my school years, I used to dread fitness and sports.

⚪️ I joined the Army at 19 to push myself beyond my limits.

⚪️ After leaving the Army at 25, I became a certified fitness trainer.

⚪️ In 2012, I created my YouTube channel to provide free workouts that people could do at home and teach through my channel the true health benefits of exercise.

⚪️ In 2017, I was invited to give a TedTalk at Surrey University about my vision of teaching and providing free workouts for everyone.

⚪️ Today, now my YouTube Channel has 2.3 million subscribers all benefiting from free home fitness, and I can reach so many people worldwide and spread the positive message of how exercise is key for our health ❤️

So the moral of the story is: never give up on your dreams. 
I look back at all the rejections I had over the years and I am so grateful as it taught me to FIND MY OWN PATH and not wait for an opportunity instead I created my own 🙅🏼‍♀️
